Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja The successor development plan being prepared to replace the 2017-2020 Economic and Growth Recovery Plan will address challenges posed by the COVID-19 pandemic and similar future unforeseen concerns, the Federal Government has said. Nigeria’s 2017-2020 ERGP is a medium term plan developed by the current government for the purpose of restoring economic growth, while leveraging the ingenuity and the resilience of the Nigerian people. In his remarks at the Sustainable Development Goals stakeholders’ virtual national validation workshop, the Minister of State for Budget and National Planning, Clement Agba, said the successor development plan to the ERGP had reached advanced stage. Copyright PUNCH.
